<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Multidistrict Lit Man § 5:27<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Multidistrict Litigation Manual</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20190501"><bop/><bos/>May 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>David F. Herr[<footnote.reference refid="If4212cb16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">a0</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I97b7f560933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Part</label.name><label.designator>I.</label.designator><headtext>Handling Cases Before the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><prop.head toc-guid="Id8e3eb20933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>5.</label.designator><headtext>Factors in Deciding Whether Transfer Is Appropriate</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="I94f12b7be1e311da9c26e67ca3b71335"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>5:27.</label.designator><headtext>Specific factors articulated by the Panel—Likelihood of multiple and conflicting pretrial rulings</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The Panel has specifically considered the likelihood of either burdensome or conflicting pretrial rulings as a factor requiring transfer. <eos/><bos/>This factor is essentially a threshold requirement under the statute.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If42217106b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">1</footnote.reference>] It is also, however, a factor that affects the Panel&apos;s exercise of discretion in cases where transfer may be appropriate.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If42217126b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">2</footnote.reference>]</paratext><eos/><eop/></para><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The potential for conflicting decisions on class certification is a category unto itself.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If4223e206b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">3</footnote.reference>] The Panel has expressed similar concern about expert witnesses and potentially inconsistent Daubert rulings.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If4223e226b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">4</footnote.reference>]</paratext><eos/><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="If4212cb16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>a0</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Maslon Edelman Borman &amp; Brand, LLP, Minneapolis, Minnesota.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><footnote.block><footnote ID="If42217106b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The role of this factor under the statute is discussed in <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs5:2" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If42217116b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">§ 5:2</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If42217126b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See, e.g.</ital>, <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="1986162810" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" w-pinpoint-page="189" ID="I7a4d20116b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re Dow Chemical Co. Sarabond Products Liability Litigation, 650 F. Supp. 187, 189 (J.P.M.L. 1986)</cite.query>; <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="1985161658" w-seq-number="00002" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" w-pinpoint-page="635" ID="I7a4d20136b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re Air Crash at Dallas/Fort Worth Airport on Aug. 2, 1985, 623 F. Supp. 634, 635 (J.P.M.L. 1985)</cite.query>; <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="1977106312" w-seq-number="00003" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" w-pinpoint-page="1034" ID="I7a4d20156b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re General Tire &amp; Rubber Co. Securities Litigation, 429 F. Supp. 1032, 1034 (J.P.M.L. 1977)</cite.query>; <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="1974107611" w-seq-number="00004" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" w-pinpoint-page="613" ID="I7a4d20176b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re Roadway Exp., Inc. Employment Practices Litigation, 384 F. Supp. 612, 613 (J.P.M.L. 1974)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If4223e206b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>3</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See</ital> <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs5:24" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If4223e216b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">§ 5:24</cite.query>, above.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If4223e226b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>4</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See, e.g.,</ital> <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="2039935869" w-seq-number="00005" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0007903" ID="I7a4e31816b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re FCA US LLC Monostable Electronic Gearshift Litigation, 214 F. Supp. 3d 1354 (U.S.J.P.M.L. 2016)</cite.query>; <cite.query w-src-number="0304914029" w-serial-number="2038641949" w-seq-number="00006" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0007903" ID="I7a4e31836b3e11e99f73e2698c313519">In re Viagra (Sildenafil Citrate) Products Liability Litigation, 176 F. Supp. 3d 1377 (U.S.J.P.M.L. 2016)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></footnote.block><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>Westlaw. © 2019 Thomson Reuters.  <eos/><bos/>No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. <eos/><bos/>Works.<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>MDLITMAN § 5:27<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
